  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nlibp2p-tcp closes streams upon 30 seconds on inactivity (both inbound and outbound), and will close the connection\r\nhttps://github.com/libp2p/js-libp2p-tcp/blob/ceac538e1e08f74fe6e509ca2fa5546876b7f51e/src/socket-to-conn.ts#L62\r\n\r\nlibp2p-tcp uses Socket setTimeout() which is a NodeJS feature from it's data stream. So timeout means:\r\n- No data seen in that stream for $timeout miliseconds\r\n\r\nCurrent sim tests suffer from this timeouts:\r\n- Are really the nodes not sending any data for 30 seconds?\r\n- Is the 30 seconds timeout a good value?\r\n- Why is this issue only showing up now?\r\n- There should be metrics reporting the reasons to severe connections",
